🌐 The Big Picture First
Think of the agent ecosystem like a city that runs itself:

Every agent = a citizen with a job, a home (Docker container), and a way to talk to others

Redis = the city radio — fast broadcast between agents

PostgreSQL = the city memory — permanent records

The Crew Orchestrator = the city mayor — assigns work, tracks it

The Healer = the city paramedic — keeps everyone alive

🧠 THE CORE LIFE PRINCIPLES (All Agents Live By These)
Every Hyper Agent follows a shared constitution:

Communicate via shared messaging — Redis pub/sub or the Crew API

Have a health endpoint — /health must always respond, no excuses

Be stateless where possible — store nothing in memory long-term; use PostgreSQL/Redis

Register on startup — ping the Crew Orchestrator, say "I'm alive and I am [role]"

Accept tasks via standard JSON schema — one format, every agent

Report back — every task gets a status update: in_progress, done, failed

Self-heal or escalate — try once to fix yourself, then call the Healer Agent

Play nice — never block another agent's work; use async everywhere

